    About this hotel

    In a charming plant-filled complex with wooden shutters, this laid-back riad is a minute's walk from a bus stop and a 5-minute walk from vibrant market stalls at the Medina of Marrakesh. It's 2 km from Koutoubia Mosque.

    Check-in time: 2:00 PM
    Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    We stayed at Riad La Ferme Medina Sept. 25th – Oct. 2nd 2022. The total cost for the week was just a little over $500 US before local taxes. This was our first visit to Marrakech and if we ever go back this is where we will stay. This is a Fantastic Property in a convenient location right in the center of the Medina. It has a very good, reasonably priced restaurant on site that is open all day and breakfast was included with our stay. I took a photo of the menu and will include it with my pictures. The entire property is a perfect blend of the old and the new. The rooms were very clean and gave you a feeling of old Morocco but with modern amenities. The entry door and windows in the room can be opened to the courtyard for an open-air feeling. The courtyard is like a rainforest with many plants and water features and is where we had our meals. Some people preferred to have their breakfast on the terrace outside of their room and the staff gladly delivered.
    We got to know the owner and most of the staff during our stay. They are all so friendly and helpful in every way. We had a unique problem with a luggage mix up at the airport. We don’t speak their language and our cell phones were very limited but the staff at La Ferme did all they could to help us get through it. When it was time to leave they arranged a car to take us to the airport and just added it to our hotel charges. No matter what you needed they would do everything possible to accommodate you… and did it with a smile.

    Medina

    Hammam bath houses and covered spice and textile souks line the maze of cobblestoned lanes in the Medina, which occupies Marrakesh’s original fortified citadel. At night, Jemaa el-Fna square teems with snake charmers, folk dancers, and street food vendors serving all manner of food. Bahia Palace and Le Jardin Secret are 19th-century complexes open to the public, with ornate courtyards, mosaics, and gardens.

    About this hotel

    In a charming plant-filled complex with wooden shutters, this laid-back riad is a minute's walk from a bus stop and a 5-minute walk from vibrant market stalls at the Medina of Marrakesh. It's 2 km from Koutoubia Mosque. …

    Featuring rustic-chic accents, the 5 down-to-earth rooms provide TVs and en suite bathrooms. Some have bathtubs and/or balconies.

    There's a restaurant with a garden terrace. Breakfast is available.
